770
00:35:59,345 --> 00:36:01,479
You hired that kid
to amuse yourself,

771
00:36:01,547 --> 00:36:03,047
and now I'm vulnerable.

772
00:36:03,115 --> 00:36:05,416
And after everything
that's happened,

773
00:36:05,484 --> 00:36:10,522
you still couldn't put me
ahead of you.

774
00:36:10,589 --> 00:36:12,590
The client asked me
to save his dream.

775
00:36:12,658 --> 00:36:14,058
I did.

776
00:36:14,126 --> 00:36:16,060
You're actually starting
to believe your own bullshit.

777
00:36:16,128 --> 00:36:18,696
- Jessica, come on.
- Just go, Harvey.

778
00:36:18,764 --> 00:36:23,067
I will get past this.
I will move on.

779
00:36:23,135 --> 00:36:26,804
And I will accept that
at the end of the day,

780
00:36:26,872 --> 00:36:30,408
that I am alone in this.

781
00:36:54,433 --> 00:36:56,901
- Hey.
- Hey.

782
00:36:56,969 --> 00:36:58,002
Four blocks from the office,

783
00:36:58,070 --> 00:36:59,904
I sort of love
this clandestine thing.

784
00:36:59,972 --> 00:37:01,239
Kind of sexy, right? [Laughs]

785
00:37:01,307 --> 00:37:03,441
[Laughs] Oh, thank you.

786
00:37:03,509 --> 00:37:05,209
Look, I was thinking about
what you said last night,

787
00:37:05,277 --> 00:37:07,812
and you're right,
I have been so scared about

788
00:37:07,880 --> 00:37:11,482
taking the LSATs, I know I have.
Rachel, I, uh...

789
00:37:11,550 --> 00:37:14,252
there's something
I need to tell you.

790
00:37:14,320 --> 00:37:17,989
We can't do this anymore.

791
00:37:18,057 --> 00:37:19,424
Okay.

792
00:37:19,491 --> 00:37:20,692
It's not that I don't want to...

793
00:37:20,759 --> 00:37:22,026
Wait, where's this coming from?

794
00:37:22,094 --> 00:37:24,195
Because last night you... eh...
this was all your idea.

795
00:37:24,263 --> 00:37:25,430
- I know.
- So?

796
00:37:25,497 --> 00:37:28,600
Collin McCarthy?

797
00:37:28,667 --> 00:37:30,668
- What about Collin McCarthy?
- You dated him.

798
00:37:30,736 --> 00:37:32,503
- Yeah, I know.
- He was a first-year.

799
00:37:32,571 --> 00:37:34,305
You broke up with him,
and his work went off a cliff,

800
00:37:34,373 --> 00:37:35,807
and then he was fired
two months later.

801
00:37:35,874 --> 00:37:37,075
That's why you don't want
to date someone

802
00:37:37,142 --> 00:37:38,476
from the office, right?
This is ridiculous.

803
00:37:38,544 --> 00:37:39,877
He has nothing to do
with you and me.

804
00:37:39,945 --> 00:37:41,412
But he does.

805
00:37:41,480 --> 00:37:44,916
I know that you and I both
want this, okay, but...

806
00:37:44,984 --> 00:37:48,853
chances are,
I'm gonna screw it up.

807
00:37:48,921 --> 00:37:50,154
I love my job,

808
00:37:50,222 --> 00:37:53,224
and I love...
I love working with you.

809
00:37:53,292 --> 00:37:55,159
And I'm afraid, okay?
I'm afraid that...

810
00:37:55,227 --> 00:37:58,930
that this will ruin that.

811
00:37:58,998 --> 00:38:00,264
So...

812
00:38:00,332 --> 00:38:06,270
Wow, that was a lot
of words, Mike.

813
00:38:06,338 --> 00:38:08,406
Why don't you just say it?

814
00:38:08,474 --> 00:38:10,041
You know what, actually,
don't say it.

815
00:38:10,109 --> 00:38:12,210
I can say it for you
because it doesn't take me days

816
00:38:12,277 --> 00:38:13,277
to hear your message.

817
00:38:13,345 --> 00:38:14,846
I hear your message
loud and clear.

818
00:38:14,913 --> 00:38:20,151
I'm just not good enough
for you.

819
00:38:32,898 --> 00:38:37,669
Have Norma send up
a bouquet of flowers,

820
00:38:37,736 --> 00:38:42,740
and make sure that they
repolish the cherrywood.

821
00:38:42,808 --> 00:38:46,344
It's walnut.

822
00:38:46,412 --> 00:38:51,549
I just wanted to make sure
that the place was ready.

823
00:38:51,617 --> 00:38:53,518
I had them redo the walls.

824
00:38:53,585 --> 00:38:57,522
This is taupe. Mm.

825
00:38:57,589 --> 00:38:59,657
I want it to be perfect

826
00:38:59,725 --> 00:39:03,361
for when Daniel gets back.

827
00:39:03,429 --> 00:39:05,596
You wanted something
this morning.

828
00:39:05,664 --> 00:39:07,665
I'm sorry, I was rushed.

829
00:39:07,733 --> 00:39:10,368
I'm not now.

830
00:39:10,436 --> 00:39:14,072
Do you still need me?

831
00:39:14,139 --> 00:39:16,541
No.

832
00:39:43,035 --> 00:39:45,236
Checking up on me?

833
00:39:45,304 --> 00:39:46,904
Checking in on you.

834
00:39:46,972 --> 00:39:48,773
Well, don't worry, Harvey.

835
00:39:48,841 --> 00:39:51,542
You were right, as always.

836
00:39:51,610 --> 00:39:54,011
I don't like having
to tell you to do something

837
00:39:54,079 --> 00:39:55,513
that you don't want to do.

838
00:39:55,581 --> 00:39:58,182
Why is it that I have to do
everything that you tell me to,

839
00:39:58,250 --> 00:40:02,887
but you can ignore whatever
Jessica tells you to do?

840
00:40:02,955 --> 00:40:05,289
You have plenty of time
to find the right girl, Mike.

841
00:40:05,357 --> 00:40:08,159
[Chuckles] Well, thank you.

842
00:40:08,227 --> 00:40:10,495
Guess I should get my book,
take some notes.

843
00:40:10,562 --> 00:40:12,697
Harvey Specter's dating tips.

844
00:40:12,765 --> 00:40:16,534
'Cause I'm sure you told
yourself that at 25 and 30

845
00:40:16,602 --> 00:40:19,070
and 35, and I'm sure you'll be
telling yourself that

846
00:40:19,138 --> 00:40:23,741
when you're 50.

847
00:40:23,809 --> 00:40:28,980
You know I was right.

848
00:40:29,047 --> 00:40:33,518
Doesn't make it any better.

849
00:41:10,556 --> 00:41:16,494
[Rattling]

850
00:41:25,971 --> 00:41:27,972
You're not alone in this.

851
00:41:32,644 --> 00:41:35,880
Put it over there.